==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[intermittens]]''', ''sending between'', from prefix '''[[inter-]]''', ''among'' or ''between'', plus present participle '''[[mittens]]''', ''sending'', from '''[[mittere]]''', ''send''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-intermittent.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''intermittent'''
# [[stop|Stopping]] and [[start]]ing at [[interval]]s; not [[steady]] or [[constant]]
#:''The day was cloudy with '''intermittent''' rain.''

====Translations====
*French: intermittent

